[1]
Date: Wed 13 Jul 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2016; 29(28) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?reportid=20465


Date of start of the event: 7 Jul 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 12 Jul 2016
Report date: 13 Jul 2016
Date submitted to OIE: 13 Jul 2016
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)

Outbreak 1: Odeshog, Farm, Odeshog, Ostergotlands Lan
Date of start of the outbreak: 7 Jul 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 216 / 7 / 7 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A beef cattle herd on pasture; 3 of the animals were found dead; 1 animal has undergone an autopsy and anthrax was confirmed. Additionally 4 animals have died in this herd, 3 of them are confirmed Anthrax.
[When this was posted on 13 Jul 2016, only 3 cases/deaths were reported. Further animals died and the OIE report adjusted. - Mod.MHJ]

