New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Vadstena, Vadstena, Ostergotlands Lan
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Jul 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases/ / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 140 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: This is a beef cattle herd, not a milk cattle herd. 1 cow was found dead on the pasture. Sample was confirmed the same day by PCR.

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: The animals are believed to have been infected by spores from soil on the pasture.

