New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Vadstena, Vadstena, Ostergotlands Lan
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Jul 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 3 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: On 27 Jul 2016, a 14 years old Warmblood gelding was found dead on pasture. No obvious signs of disease were found and the horse had appeared healthy when observed on the evening before. Blood samples were taken from the dead horse the same day, analysed with PCR technique, and were found positive to _Bacillus anthracis_. Another 2 Warmblood horses on the same pasture were found healthy. These 2 were treated with antibiotic. All 3 horses had been moved to the pasture on 16 Jul [2016].

Epidemiology: [as before]

